self.title: CDISC SDTM Urinary System Test Name Terminology

definition: A terminology codelist to describe the test name for examinations of the urinary system.
name: Urinary System Test Name
preferredTerm: CDISC SDTM Urinary System Test Name Terminology

terms.definition: The volume of blood per unit time passing through a specified location, such as a point in a blood vessel or an entire organ.
A measurement of the color of a biological specimen.
The condition of the donated organ or tissue. (NCI)
An indication as to whether hematoma has occurred.
The linear extent in space from one end of something to the other end, or the extent of something from beginning to end. (NCI)
A measurement of the total number of renal arteries.
A measurement of the total number of renal veins.
An indication as to whether surgical damage has occurred.
An observation, assessment or examination of the urinary system.
